  %h5 Entering Other Costs:

  %p Other costs are designed to help you identify where your organization classifies activities other than those that fit into activities that you’ve categorized.  These are designed to illustrate how expenses for managing projects and activities at a central level are structured.

  %p You can detail other costs at the project or at the organization level.  To detail the expenses for one or more project, create a new flow, and select the number of projects the detail applies to.  To detail expenses for all projects, select all checkboxes. To detail costs that fall outside all projects, select no boxes. Once you have created a flow, click on the “detail cost areas” link and classify these costs.

